flowRoot.flowPara: Upgrade notification is shown when a new version is available for download. Notification is shown two or three times, at a 2/3 day interval.
Upgrade notifications shouldn't be shown at a similar time to update ones.
Upgrades are not counted towards the update counter.
The "Software is up to date" label and check mark icon are not shown when an upgrade is available.
"Learn more" opens a web page of the distribution's choosing.
If there are apps or add-ons that aren't compatible with, or aren't available for, the next version, a banner is shown with a link to more information.
Download progress is shown as a progress bar.
Updates to the current version can be installed while an upgrade is in the process of being downloaded.
A notification is displayed once the download is complete.
After restart and upgrade:
1. If the upgrade contains new features that users need to (a) be explicitly told about (b) be able to opt in/out of, or (c) be able to configure, initial setup needs to run andpresent them.

2. Once in the session, we should show information about the new version - positive advertising of new features, how great the new version is, and tips and tricks on how to use it. We have been focusing on Yelp to provide this for new installs (bug 740304). If it gains the ability to show a "What's New" section, this could be displayed after the upgrade has taken place.
